page.title: 09Georgeham Church
page.content: It is believed that Georgeham church was first built in 1231.Since then there have been 45 rectors starting with Robert de Edington to the presant rector Bernard John Bedford Carr.He's been there since 1974.There is none of the church built in 1231 left because it was completly rebuilt in 1762. All stain glass windows are in memory of someone. The oldest one was put up in 1866.There are also many plaques put up in the church commemorating people.There are 33 pipes in the organ.Because in 1231 there were no newspapers all important facts were put on plaques in the church such as the comet in 1680. The church is painted in quiet colours and is quiet itself.
